# ${project_name} — TaskOps

> Prefix: `${prefix}` | DB: `taskops.db`

⚠️ TaskOps only manages `taskops.db` and this file.

---

## Agent Rules

### 1. Operation Recording

| Event | Command |
|-------|---------|
| Start task | `op start <T-ID> --platform <claude_code\|gemini_cli>` |
| Major milestone | `op progress <T-ID> --summary "..."` |
| Complete | `op complete <T-ID> --summary "..."` |
| Error | `op error <T-ID> --summary "..."` |
| Blocked | `op interrupt <T-ID> --summary "..."` |

Call `op progress` after: implementing a component, creating/modifying a key file, writing/passing tests, resolving a bug, or switching tasks.

### 2. Resource Registration

Register every file created/modified before marking a task done:

```bash
python -m cli --db taskops.db resource add <T-ID> --path <path> --type <input|output|intermediate|reference> --desc "..."
```

